{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:proverbs.24",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 24,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 24 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:1",
      "text": "Seek not to be like evil men, neither desire to be with them:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:2",
      "text": "Because their mind studieth robberies, and their lips speak deceits.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:3",
      "text": "By wisdom the house shall be built, and by prudence it shall be strengthened.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:4",
      "text": "By instruction the storerooms shall be filled with all precious and most beautiful wealth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:5",
      "text": "A wise man is strong: and a knowing man, stout and valiant.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:6",
      "text": "Because war is managed by due ordering: and there shall be safety where there are many counsels.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:7",
      "text": "Wisdom is too high for a fool; in the gate he shall not open his mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:8",
      "text": "He that deviseth to do evils, shall be called a fool.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:9",
      "text": "The thought of a fool is sin: and the detractor is the abomination of men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:10",
      "text": "If thou lose hope, being weary in the day of distress, thy strength shall be diminished.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:11",
      "text": "Deliver them that are led to death: and those that are drawn to death, forbear not to deliver.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:12",
      "text": "If thou say: I have not strength enough: he that seeth into the heart, he understandeth, and nothing deceiveth the keeper of thy soul, and he shall render to a man according to his works.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:13",
      "text": "Eat honey, my son, because it is good, and the honeycomb most sweet to thy throat.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:14",
      "text": "So also is the doctrine of wisdom to thy soul: which when thou hast found, thou shalt have hope in the end, and thy hope shall not perish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:15",
      "text": "Lie not in wait, nor seek after wickedness in the house of the just, nor spoil his rest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:16",
      "text": "For a just man shall fall seven times, and shall rise again: but the wicked shall fall down into evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:17",
      "text": "When thy enemy shall fall, be not glad, and in his ruin let not thy heart rejoice:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:18",
      "text": "Lest the Lord see, and it displease him, and he turn away his wrath from him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:19",
      "text": "Contend not with the wicked, nor seek to be like the ungodly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:20",
      "text": "For evil men have no hope of things to come, and the lamp of the wicked shall be put out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:21",
      "text": "My son, fear the Lord, and the king: and have nothing to do with detractors.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:22",
      "text": "For their destruction shall rise suddenly: and who knoweth the ruin of both?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:23",
      "text": "These things also to the wise: It is not good to have respect to persons in judgment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:24",
      "text": "They that say to the wicked man: Thou art just: shall be cursed by the people, and the tribes shall abhor them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:25",
      "text": "They that rebuke him shall be praised: and a blessing shall come upon them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:26",
      "text": "He shall kiss the lips, who answereth right words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:27",
      "text": "Prepare thy work without, and diligently till thy ground: that afterward thou mayst build thy house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:28",
      "text": "Be not witness without cause against thy neighbour: and deceive not any man with thy lips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:29",
      "text": "Say not: I will do to him as he hath done to me: I will render to every one according to his work.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:30",
      "text": "I passed by the field of the slothful man, and by the vineyard of the foolish man:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:31",
      "text": "And behold it was all filled with nettles, and thorns had covered the face thereof, and the stone wall was broken down.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.32",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:32",
      "text": "Which when I had seen, I laid it up in my heart, and by the example I received instruction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.33",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:33",
      "text": "Thou wilt sleep a little, said I, thou wilt slumber a little, thou wilt fold thy hands a little to rest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.24.34",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 24:34",
      "text": "And poverty shall come to thee as a runner, and beggary as an armed man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
